biz.sudden.designCoordination.teamFormation.dataStructures
Class ConcreteSupplyNetwork

java.lang.Object
  biz.sudden.designCoordination.teamFormation.dataStructures.ConcreteSupplyNetwork
All Implemented Interfaces:
Connectable
public class ConcreteSupplyNetwork
extends java.lang.Object
implements Connectable

A combination of an abstract supply network with a single set of candidate teams. I'm doing it this way rather than using one ASN with many teams linked to it to allow for situations where there are multiple ASN's in use at once. Some slightly fancy interfaces on this method :) (with more to come later)

mcassmc

public ConcreteSupplyNetwork(AbstractSupplyNetwork ASNin,

Yes holding both the ASN & the roleNode/Supplier link separately is a bit clunky. But the ASN is being kept since it contains non role specific information and is just all round useful anyway. The attached rankings should (I expect currently) either be positive or -MinValue if they've not been set yet.
